<br>
Greetings esteemed OoT friends,<br>
<br>
The following provides you with current guild  policy on:<br>
 - Keys<br>
 - Raids<br>
 - Alternates in Oracles<br>
<br>
<br>
KEYS<br>
An Initiate to Oracles must have their keys to portal rings (example: GD, WL, CS) and to Charisis (aka Howling Stones) and Sebillis in order to be considered eligible for full membership in the guild.  <br>
<br>
RAIDS<br>
At least one formal guild raid is planned per weekend (see definition).  All Initiates and members who are online during a planned weekend guild event are expected to participate. Among the Membership Eligibilty criteria is Raid participation - Initiates who do not participate may compromise their full membership eligibiity. <br>
<br>
Weekend Definition: Friday 7pm Central to Sunday 12pm Central time.<br>
<br>
While your participation is encouraged and appreciated, it is optional for Guild events that occur outside of the defined weekend time frame.<br>
<br>
Basically, you may use your EQ time from Sunday 12:01pm central time to Friday 6:59 pm Central in any manner you wish, to work on epic, skills, experience and so forth.  Beginning at 7pm Friday and through Sunday 12pm is guild time and any events held during that time requires the participation of every member online.<br>
<br>
ALTERNATES<br>
Oracles of Truth is a guild for those who are of level 50 or higher.  Disciple of Truth is our sister guild and was formed for characters of level 20 to level 49.  Clerics in OoT may place an alternate in OoT of any level to faciliate communication during Raid related Corpse Recovery.  All other members should place their alternates of level lower than 50 in Disciple of Truth.  As per our charter, members should have no alternates placed in guilds other than in OoT or in DoT.<br>
<br>
Please feel free to ask me or any other officer any question you have about this information.<br>
<br>
Your officers include: Cyrisse/Ammadien, Tempust, Balterzar/Kylean, Whallil, Dsenier.<br>
<br>
Cheers!<br>
<br>
